      ],
      "rating": 3,
      "active": true,
      "content": "[Financial Performance]\nPre-profitability biotech. FY2025 revenue $3.5M (milestone-based, no major milestones). Cash burn $345.9M. Cash & investments $1.98B. R&D $265.3M (down from $320.7M). Net loss $581.6M ($6.47/share).\nKey milestone: CTX310 Phase 1b data published in NEJM. Pediatric CASGEVY data positive at ASH.\n[Management Tone]\nBullish",
      "source_doc": null
    },
    {
      "title": "FY2025 vs FY2024 — Narrative Evolution Analysis",
      "note_type": null,
      "date": null,
      "quarter": null,
      "tags": [
        "strategy"
      ],
      "rating": 3,
      "active": true,
      "content": "[Narrative Drift]\nEvolved from gene editing pioneer to broader biopharmaceutical company. Expanded beyond CRISPR/Cas9 to include siRNA (Sirius partnership) and SyNTase technologies. Added Eli Lilly collaboration for zugocabtagene geleucel.\n[Red Flags]\n• CTX131 CD70 program no longer emphasized\n• Expanded macroeconomic risk factors (inflation, tariffs, geopolitical tensions)\n• Type 1 diabetes folded into regenerative medicine franchise",
      "source_doc": null
    }
  ],
